Gunmen Monday evening kidnapped a lawyer, Musbahu Adetunbi, at Iwaraja via Ilesa in Osun State. The Ibadan-based lawyer was said to be on his way to the Court of Appeal in Akure, Ondo State, when he was kidnapped. The vice chairman of the Nigerian Bar Association, Ibadan branch, Ibrahim Lawal, confirmed the incident yesterday, saying “The sad news of Musibau Adetumbi’s abduction was received with shock. He was travelling with two of his lawyers from Ibadan to Akure. Only Musibau and the driver of his Honda Civic were abducted.” He called on the security agencies to ensure the release of the lawyer and his driver. Gunmen kidnap lawyer in Osun Beyond Chief Olu Falae’s kidnap Gunmen abduct female lawyer in Kogi